
[1]delirium

   DELIRIUM, n. [L. To wander in mind, to rave; to make balks in plowing,
   that is, to err, wander, miss.]

   A state in which the ideas of a person are wild, irregular and
   unconnected, or do not correspond with the truth or with external
   objects; a roving or wandering of the mind; disorder of the intellect.
   Fevers often produce delirium.

   An alienation of mind connected with fever.

   Symptomatic derangement, or that which is dependent on some other
   disease, in distinction from idiopathic derrangement or mania.
